    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lithographs obtained by means of lithographic chalk, also called crayon. Before its application the lithographic stone was roughened by grinding fine sand over its surface.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000116/V&amp;A Word Image</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000016051/Gascoigne, How to Identify Prints (1986)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Lithografieën die men maakt met lithografische kalk. Vóór gebruik werd de lithografische steen opgeruwd door het oppervlak te schuren met fijn zand.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>使用石版畫粉筆(或稱為蠟筆)製成的石版畫。在使用之前，會用細砂在石印灰岩表面上磨成粗糙面備用。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
